    <h2 id="why-collagen">Why Collagen Supplements Work for Skin — The Science in 2026</h2>

    <p>Collagen is the most abundant protein in your body and the primary structural component of your skin. It gives skin its firmness, elasticity, and youthful appearance. Starting at age 25, your body produces roughly <strong>1% less collagen every year</strong>, and by age 50 you have lost about 30% of your dermal collagen. This decline drives the visible signs of aging: fine lines, wrinkles, sagging, and thin, dry skin. Supplemental collagen offers a clinically validated way to slow and partially reverse this process.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">+28%</span>
