    <h2 id="how-to-choose">How to Choose the Right Collagen Supplement for Your Skin Goals</h2>

    <div class="num-steps">
      <div class="num-step"><span class="num">1</span><div><strong>Identify your primary goal.</strong> Wrinkle reduction → Verisol-based products (Olly). General elasticity → Type I + III (Vital Proteins, Garden of Life). Hydration → pair collagen with hyaluronic acid (NeoCell). Full anti-aging → add resveratrol (Reserveage) or multi-type (Ancient Nutrition).</div></div>
      <div class="num-step"><span class="num">2</span><div><strong>Choose your format honestly.</strong> Do you actually drink coffee or smoothies daily? Powder. Do you want zero prep and travel friendly? Gummy or capsule. Do you prioritize maximum dose? Powder every time. The "best" format is the one you will take for 12+ weeks.</div></div>
      <div class="num-step"><span class="num">3</span><div><strong>Verify Type I + III content.</strong> For skin-only goals, Type I + III is all that matters. Type II is for joints. Multi-type is fine if you want joint benefits alongside skin, but pure Type I + III is more efficient per dollar for skin.</div></div>
      <div class="num-step"><span class="num">4</span><div><strong>Check for vitamin C.</strong> Collagen synthesis requires vitamin C as an enzymatic cofactor. Products that include it (NeoCell, Olly, Vital Proteins Gummies) have a mechanistic edge. If your product does not include it, take a vitamin C gummy or fruit alongside.</div></div>
      <div class="num-step"><span class="num">5</span><div><strong>Demand third-party testing.</strong> USP Verified (Nature Made), NSF Certified for Sport (Vital Proteins), or Informed Sport (Sports Research) are the highest standards. Avoid brands with no testing disclosure — collagen can contain heavy metals from poor-quality bovine sourcing.</div></div>
      <div class="num-step"><span class="num">6</span><div><strong>Commit to 12 weeks.</strong> Collagen is not a one-week fix. Clinical trials show first results at 4 weeks (hydration), elasticity gains at 8 weeks, and wrinkle improvements at 12 weeks. Stopping causes regression within 12 weeks. Budget for a full quarter minimum.</div></div>
    </div>

